{"word":"ἕτοιμος","slug":"ἕτοιμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἕτοιμος, η, ον</el></b> [later form of <el>ἑτοίμος</el>; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> unclear] of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> and things <b>ready, prepared <a href='B:470 22:4'>Mt 22:4</a>, <a href='B:470 22:8'>8</a>; <a href='B:470 25:10'>25:10</a>; <a href='B:480 14:15'>Mk 14:15</a>; <a href='B:490 12:40'>Lk 12:40</a>; <a href='B:500 7:6'>J 7:6</a>; <a href='B:510 23:15'>Ac 23:15</a>; <a href='B:630 3:1'>Tit 3:1</a>; <a href='B:670 1:5'>1 Pt 1:5</a>; <a href='B:670 3:15'>3:15</a>.—</b><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a> ἑτοίμῳ ἔχειν = be ready<b> <a href='B:540 10:6'>2 Cor 10:6</a>;</b> τὰ ἕτοιμα = things already done <b><a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ vs.\">vs.</a> 16.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἑτοιμασία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἑτοίμως\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}